curam.util.client.model

Class FormItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.client.model.FormItem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class FormItem
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A form item represents a single item in a form. The item has a target path, a domain name and a label. It will not have a value until the form is submitted. When rendering fields in a form, you must create form items to represent each of the form controls. When a form is submitted the form items will be reconstructed automatically, values will be set, and they will be passed to the appropriate DomainMarshal for processing.
    See Also:
